defs.docs:
# Rustls - a modern TLS library
 Rustls is a TLS library that aims to provide a good level of cryptographic security,
 requires no configuration to achieve that security, and provides no unsafe features or
 obsolete cryptography.

 in memory.  It enforces a limit on the number of entries
 to bound memory usage.

Make a new ClientSessionMemoryCache.  `size` is the

Returns the latest value for `key`.  Returns `None`
 if there's no such value.

A trait for the ability to choose a certificate chain and
 private key for the purposes of client authentication.

With the server-supplied acceptable issuers in `acceptable_issuers`,
 the server's supported signature schemes in `sigschemes`,
 return a certificate chain and signing key to authenticate.

defs.docs:
Common configuration for (typically) all connections made by
 a program.

defs.name: ciphersuites
defs.docs: List of ciphersuites, in preference order.

defs.name: root_store
defs.docs: Collection of root certificates.

defs.name: alpn_protocols
defs.docs:
Which ALPN protocols we include in our client hello.
 If empty, no ALPN extension is sent.

defs.name: session_persistence
defs.docs: How we store session data or tickets.

defs.name: mtu
defs.docs: Our MTU.  If None, we don't limit TLS message sizes.

defs.name: client_auth_cert_resolver
defs.docs: How to decide what client auth certificate/keys to use.

defs.name: enable_tickets
defs.docs:
Whether to support RFC5077 tickets.  You must provide a working
 `session_persistence` member for this to have any meaningful
 effect.

defs.name: versions
defs.docs:
Supported versions, in no particular order.  The default
 is all supported versions.

defs.name: ct_logs
defs.docs:
Collection of certificate transparency logs.
 If this collection is empty, then certificate transparency
 checking is disabled.

defs.name: enable_sni
defs.docs:
Whether to send the Server Name Indication (SNI) extension
 during the client handshake.

defs.name: key_log
defs.docs:
How to output key material for debugging.  The default
 does nothing.

defs.name: enable_early_data
defs.docs:
Whether to send data on the first flight ("early data") in
 TLS 1.3 handshakes.

defs.name: new
defs.docs:
Make a `ClientConfig` with a default set of ciphersuites,
 no root certificates, no ALPN protocols, and no client auth.

defs.name: supports_version
defs.docs:
We support a given TLS version if it's quoted in the configured
 versions *and* at least one ciphersuite for this version is
 also configured.

defs.name: set_protocols
defs.docs:
Set the ALPN protocol list to the given protocol names.
 Overwrites any existing configured protocols.
 The first element in the `protocols` list is the most
 preferred, the last is the least preferred.

defs.name: set_persistence
defs.docs: Sets persistence layer to `persist`.

defs.name: set_mtu
defs.docs:
Sets MTU to `mtu`.  If None, the default is used.
 If Some(x) then x must be greater than 5 bytes.

Returns an `io::Write` implementor you can write bytes to
 to send TLS1.3 early data (a.k.a. "0-RTT data") to the server.
